caption: I work downtown, and this is my go to restaurant for lunch, as well as for many other city workers I see there regularly. I see politicians, cops, etc. so it's a place to be trusted. Large buffet with a variety of options, as well as a grill with a large menu. I can honestly say everything I've had was great, and I eat there regularly. Prices are very reasonable, fountain drinks as well as a large selection of bottled beverages, and small items (snacks, pastries, etc.) Highly recommend if you're looking for something affordable and casual.

Great location. Eat in cafe or carry out. Families welcome. Terrific value, helpful staff. Breakfast, then lunch til well after noon. Beverages galore. Terrific variety of food. Well prepared, nicely spiced with a light touch. From hearty savory All-American... to the healthy fruit and salad and veggie bar... to Asian delights and candies and fresh baked sweet treats, this place is my first stop. Sandwiches and platters made to order. Lots and lots of regular customers, all kinds. Nice cross-section of city and suburban folks.

Typical expensive buy-by-the-pound Asian spot selling breakfast and lunch items that sit out on steamers..there is also a cold salad section at lunch time also. There is also a deli counter where you can choose made-to-order breakfast, sandwiches, wraps, etc. They also usually have chicken noodle soup (LOTS of noodles, celery and carrots - a LITTLE bit of shredded chicken). The food is decent..the french fries are delish (from the deli) and inexpensive (a large is $1.99) as are the sticky wings, roasted cauliflower and spicy broccoli/stringbeans on the per pound station.
